Notebook[{
Cell["18. Split-Welded Boundary Invariance", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"32986c71-d81e-429b-8d5e-d57bd24553ce"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook tests exact toy families aligned with the split note: \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d72c70cc-777c-45d5-a4c5-8947d8c2b541"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "inherited ledger sector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "A", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cc19150b-cfeb-40cd-a4d3-da39d60cd787"],
 ","
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"90d638d1-b467-4c44-8bde-4e20504ad9a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "completion/newborn sector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["B", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "B", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a0166a27-c868-44d6-a4eb-97726c1ccc1f"],
 ","
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"85e864b3-fcde-4aa3-a360-e00b78a45497"],

Cell["controlled split unitary", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e44547e3-c84b-4f91-9795-a391304e8685"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox[
          StyleBox["U", "TI"], 
          StyleBox["split", FontSlant -> "Plain"]], "\[LongEqual]", 
         UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          StyleBox["i", "TI"], LimitsPositioning -> True], 
         SubsuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPi]", 
          StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
          RowBox[{"(", 
            StyleBox["A", "TI"], ")"}]], "\[CircleTimes]", 
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["U", "TI"], 
          StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
          RowBox[{"(", 
            StyleBox["B", "TI"], ")"}]], ","}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "U_{\\mathrm{split}} = \\sum_i \\Pi_i^{(A)} \\otimes U_i^{(B)},", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d38f6c97-0157-4e4f-973b-812065aefe0b"]
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"14e59066-abbd-4166-ae60-075848898071"],

Cell["\<\
welded boundary generators and ambiguity directions carried by the same \
ledger histories.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e91c9919-6b41-4793-8ca5-f07f85ac5e31"],

Cell["Family 1: safe off-diagonal ambiguity", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"69292e92-bee6-4023-9ae6-8cbbc53146ff"],

Cell["\<\
Here the ambiguity is purely ledger-off-diagonal. Controlled projection kills \
it exactly, so the induced controlled boundary derivation is class-defined on \
the nose.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f3e94478-97d5-4fdd-b1b7-1274bc48e2f2"],

Cell["\<\
This family realizes the strongest possible boundary safety condition. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0c2746fb-ab4d-4138-a6a4-317ae6767aeb"],

Cell["Family 2: unsafe visible ambiguity", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c0311414-f20f-4508-a32b-08b1148f73ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here the ambiguity has a diagonal controlled ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["B", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "B", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d9b10bd8-a24a-4cd8-a557-af1746c76a10"],
 "-component that survives controlled projection. The induced boundary \
derivation changes visibly on the controlled sector."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cd8f52c9-e4c6-4d31-b750-e76d6652e92f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the required exact countermodel showing that classical ledger \
endpoints alone do ",
 StyleBox["not",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " imply full microscopic calibration invariance."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1ae739d0-57dd-40d1-a5e6-7c13ce913c4c"],

Cell["It also gives the operator/expectation separation: ", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1002a92e-f537-4557-8b0c-95ee36a2b883"],

Cell["operator-level visibility survives,", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3036fa39-bbce-4d44-84e3-5803530a9616"],

Cell["\<\
expectation-level invisibility can still hold on diagonal boundary-classical \
states.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f7abcc81-8bca-41b8-8fa7-f147a6fff1bc"],

Cell["Family 3: borderline null-ideal family", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5f4a107e-faf2-4680-84c6-1c0c7e4b3390"],

Cell["\<\
Here the ambiguity survives controlled projection but lands entirely in the \
chosen boundary null ideal. The ambiguity is therefore invisible modulo that \
ideal, while the base controlled derivation remains nonzero on the quotient.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e4444ae6-9517-47a0-8a20-3fb28958b3fb"],

Cell["This is the key exact nontrivial example for the sprint. ", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fcd25387-a418-46fc-9576-b99836971457"],

Cell["Outcome", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0543b7fc-80d0-4e12-a88f-c867ec0099b8"],

Cell["\<\
The split+welded restriction does not give unconditional invariance. It gives \
a sharp controlled criterion: \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"774aa0ef-bb9f-43e2-8801-7ef11f2b8dde"],

Cell["off-diagonal ledger ambiguity is harmless,", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4c024941-0b5c-456e-b4ee-e6cfe01727a0"],

Cell["\<\
diagonal controlled ambiguity is the only possible obstruction,\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2c3df4dd-1628-498e-96d1-3df0f036c832"],

Cell["\<\
if that controlled ambiguity is null-ideal valued, the derivation can remain \
nontrivial while becoming class-defined on the boundary quotient.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4dddc8f9-efe0-4371-8b99-ff5851a8b9f7"],

Cell["Status", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ba5f1ee8-3ef0-480d-92cf-697de99c9e7d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 PaneBox[
  PaneBox[
   StyleBox[
    TagBox[
     TagBox[GridBox[{
        {
         TagBox["\<\"Family / claim\"\>",
          HoldForm], 
         TagBox["\<\"Status\"\>",
          HoldForm]},
        {"\<\"Safe family gives strong operator-level invariance\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Unsafe family gives visible controlled ambiguity\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Borderline family gives nontrivial mod-null invariance\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"False overreach model blocks full microscopic invariance\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"}
       },
       GridBoxAlignment->{
        "Columns" -> {Center, {Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
       GridBoxDividers->{
        "Columns" -> {{False}}, "Rows" -> {False, True, {False}, False}},
       GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
            Offset[2.0999999999999996`]}, 
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
           Offset[0.2], {
            Offset[0.4]}, 
           Offset[0.2]}}],
      {None, OutputFormsDump`HeadedColumns}],
     Function[BoxForm`e$, 
      TableForm[
      BoxForm`e$, TableHeadings -> {None, {"Family / claim", "Status"}}]]], 
    "Text",
    StripOnInput->False,
    ShowStringCharacters->False],
   ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 5}}],
  ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 5}}]], "TextTableForm", \
"Text",ExpressionUUID->"2e9538dc-63f8-4cfa-aeb7-733518ea515e"]
},
